Bottle at home , bought at the beer market. Nice head...but no kiwi inside ;)
Ibu is only 60 but the taste is really bitter ...way above the ibu rating. Worth a try but they brew better ones.

Bottle at Mikes place , the best Jems that I had till today ....and still mediocre. No head what so ever ...even that Ive did my best , poured in a Duvel glass. Nice flavor , light body, nothing to unique. Ill go for a real Belgian Tripel next time
Bottle bought in Switzerland one year ago, Ex.30.12.14. A really nice beer , much better than expected.  Defiantly reminds me of Duvel. Worth a try.
beer_name: Abbaye de Crespin Secret Des Moines Triple

review_blob: Bottle , bought in Belgium last year. Nice head but didnt hold . Way to sweet , nothing special about this one. Another under average Belgian. Wont try it again.
33 cl bottle. Nice head , taste too sweet and you can definitely feel the alcohol. Overall it was OK .... its worth a try ... but nothing more.

beer_brewer_name: Brasserie Artisanale La Botteresse de Sur-les-Bois
review_blob: Weird beer...aged one year . Poured in a Nice Chouffe glass ...no head whatsoever  , kind of sweet but no real rich taste just sweet.  Dont think that Ill drink it again.
One of the best IPAs that I ever had. Great taste and amazing head. Delicious beer !
Pours with a nice head that disappears in less then a minute. The best Alexander that I had but overall  ...its OK for an Israeli beer but had better IPAs....its worth a try.

Bottle at home. Aged one year. Thick and fruity...some vanilla maybe
Nice beer overall....but Struise have better ones.

Can I rate it as a 0 ????
